adjectives.description: peachen (comparative more peachen, superlative most peachen)

entries.meaning: Of or resembling a peach; peachlike; having a surface like that of a peach; peachy.
examples: They were fine, stalwart-looking men, well limbed, clear of eye, and upright in shape, with that peculiar color of a ripe, rich peachen hue upon the cheek, which only a pure temperate life perfect health can place there.
